text: 服务素质不输海底捞，尤其是叫奕翔的服务员，我们用餐的时候是满座外面也有好多人在等，可是没有因为忙碌而忽略服务顾客，当我叫到奕翔需要餐具，他也立即放下手下擦桌子的工作先拿餐具给我，也时不时关注我们的茶水是否需要加茶或凉了需要再添加，他介绍的菜品也很满意，下次一定带朋友过来尝试。
textTranslated: The service quality is not inferior to that of Haidilao, especially the waiter named Yi Xiang. When we were dining, the restaurant was full and there were many people waiting outside. However, he did not neglect to serve customers because he was busy. When I asked Yi Xiang to need tableware, he immediately put down his work of cleaning the table and brought the tableware to me. He also paid attention to whether our tea needed to be added from time to time or if it had cooled down before adding more. I was also very satisfied with the dishes he introduced. I will definitely bring my friends over to try it next time.

text: 香香湖南菜是一家很棒的餐厅，食物非常美味。这里的湖南菜有着独特的辣味和香味，让人回味无穷。服务员非常友好，环境也很舒适。价格合理，分量足。强烈推荐给喜欢辣味和想品尝正宗湖南菜的朋友们。
textTranslated: Xiang Xiang Hunan Cuisine is a fantastic restaurant with delicious food. The Hunan cuisine here has a unique spicy and fragrant flavor that leaves a lasting impression. The waiters are very friendly and the environment is comfortable. The prices are reasonable and the portions are generous. Highly recommended for those who enjoy spicy food and want to experience authentic Hunan cuisine.

name: ys ys
text: 在这家湘菜馆用餐非常愉快，尤其要感谢实习经理Ocean！他在面对我们提出的一些特殊要求时表现得非常灵活，随机应变能力非常强，让人倍感贴心。无论是沟通还是服务，Ocean的态度都很温暖且专业，真正让我们感受到了优质的服务。谢谢他让我们的用餐体验更为难忘！推荐这家餐厅，也强烈推荐找Ocean帮忙！
textTranslated: It was a great pleasure to dine at this Hunan restaurant, especially thanks to the intern manager Ocean! He was very flexible and very adaptable when dealing with some of our special requests, which made us feel very considerate. Whether it is communication or service, Ocean's attitude is warm and professional, which really makes us feel the high-quality service. Thank you for making our dining experience even more memorable! I highly recommend this restaurant and also highly recommend asking Ocean for help!
title: Xiang Xiang Hunan Cuisine @ Pasir Ris Mall

name: Danny Fong
reviewContext/Recommended dishes: Green Peppers with Slice Pork, Golden Broth Sour and Spicy Fish
text:
Apparently this is a home grown brand restaurant (if i am wrong. someone please correct me). As the restaurant name its Hunan cuisine; tbh i can’t tell the difference from Yunnan, Hunan or Shanghai food but i can tell what is good and whats not.

First time here, the food is delicious, in my opinion the portions are a little small i guess the strategy is order more and try everything. we were a party of 8 and we managed to try a few more things.

What is really like is, food here is not too salty. my 2 fav is the Sauerkraut Fish and Vermicelli (we ordered the 2nd one before the first one is done). because of this we ended up ordering too much rice - one pot of it feed 5 ppl. they also serve little bag of crackers and small cups of ice cream (like HDL).

The service team is very attentive and fast and oh the dishes are served faster than McDonalds on busy day 😄. what i was told is this place is typically busy during meal times and they DON’T take reservations on weekends.

text:
I had the pleasure of dining at Xiang Xiang, food is very delicious especially the stir fried angus beef and I have to say, Amy, our waitress, made the entire experience exceptional! From the moment we were seated, she greeted us with a warm smile and a friendly demeanor that instantly put us at ease.
Amy was attentive throughout the meal, ensuring our glasses were always full and that we had everything we needed. She knew the menu inside and out, giving excellent recommendations for both food and drinks, and even accommodated a couple of special requests without hesitation. Her professionalism and efficiency were top-notch, but what really stood out was her genuine kindness and upbeat attitude.

text:
we ordered stir-fry pork, sour and spicy fish, dry tossed vermicelli, braised fresh yuba and garlic sauteed lettuce.
the white fungus in the stir-fry pork was new to us and its texture added to the mouth feel and the iberico pork was fragrant too, just a tad too oily, would go well with rice! fish was clean tasting, the manager came with new bowls for us to taste the broth as it wasn't the first dish that was served, it cleansed our palette. fresh yuba is good too! not a fan of the egg yolk but that is on us for not noticing the ingredients.

name: Jaryl Teo
text: I recently dined at Xiang Xiang and was blown away by their cauliflower dish and fried vermicelli. The cauliflower was perfectly cooked, with just the right balance of tenderness and crunch, infused with a savory sauce that had a great depth of flavor. It was a delightful surprise for a vegetable dish! The fried vermicelli was equally impressive—light, not greasy, and full of flavor with a satisfying mix of textures. Both dishes showcased the chef's attention to detail and authentic flavors. I will definitely be coming back for more!
